#### EXAMPLE 9.9

Two voltage amplifiers (each with very high input impedance and low output impedance) are available: one with a gain of $3 \mathrm{~V} / \mathrm{V}$ and $3 \mu \mathrm{~V}_{\mathrm{rms}}$ noise observed at the output; the other with a gain of $8 \mathrm{~V} / \mathrm{V}$ and $6 \mu \mathrm{~V}_{\mathrm{rms}}$ noise observed at its output. What is the input-referred noise of each amplifier? If these amplifiers are to be cascaded to achieve a gain of $24 \mathrm{~V} / \mathrm{V}$, in what order should they be placed to achieve the best noise performance? What is the resulting input-referred noise of the overall system?
